      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "station"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是站、所、局，要看搭配。police station 是警察局，train station 是火车站。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 57,
      "start": 445.999,
      "end": 455.975,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "station"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这课的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "call at the station"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "说的是 go to the police station，去警察局一趟，不是 make a phone call，也不是去火车站。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 58,
      "start": 456.325,
      "end": 467.889,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "station"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "In the letter he was asked to call at the station."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这句话解释了 Dan 为什么会紧张：a police station visit sounds serious before he knows the reason."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 59,
      "start": 468.239,
